National Security Advisor Thomas E. Donilon will be traveling to China and India to meet with leaders and discuss various bilateral, regional, and global issues of mutual concern. In China, he will meet with Vice Premier Wang Qishan and State Councilor Dai Bingguo, while in India, he will meet with National Security Advisor Shiv Shankar Menon. The discussions will focus on the U.S.-India strategic partnership and ways to enhance the relationship, including their participation in the upcoming East Asia Summit. This visit highlights the U.S. administration's commitment to increasing U.S. leadership in Asia and working with emerging powers like China and India.